snippet.textDisplay: Going through a breakup too. Happened exactly 9 weeks ago and it has been rough. It was somewhat an amicable breakup but i was extremely devastated. snippet.textDisplay:
Hey Liane,
Sometimes God has to PUSH you off the cliff so that you can FALL into the path he intended for you. We ignore the red flags because being in love can be intoxicating when it’s not healthy. We have to learn the hard way that not everyone has the capacity to take care of our hearts the way we need them to. And it’s shitty when someone realizes their shortcomings and they do shitty things, thinking it will make them feel better about themselves. It doesn’t mean the love wasn’t real or that it was all a lie. It’s that they weren’t ready to be deserving of your love.
Each day is another step closer to what is meant for you. You got this ❤️ Kaya mo to.

snippet.textDisplay: I haven't been on social media for a while, but one of the last things I remember seeing was your engagement. I'm so sorry love. I know how this feels. I truly do hope your true Prince Charming comes along and sweeps you off your feet.

snippet.textDisplay: May your heart be filled with peace and your spirit be whole. Breakups are garbage, but who you become once you realize it’s not the end of the world, is the greatest reward to look forward to. We women go through so much with our pure hearts and romantic plans for the future, and it’s normal... but guess what? Your heart was too big for him. When you give the wrong person too much, they misuse it. But if you give your all to the right person, he will invest in it and continuously add to the growth and manifestation of it all! To anyone out there who is going through a breakup or at a place where you are ready to walk away, you will be okay. God will lead you exactly where you need to be and you will grow into your own. ♥️

snippet.textDisplay: Baby, you are so beautiful and so strong. The world is crazy right now and I feel like everyone is on edge. It’s crazy it definitely feels like a movie. I also just broke up with my ex of 3 years, my first boyfriend and my first love. He cheated on me during the relationship and I didn’t find out until after we broke up. It’s a different kind of pain. You lose your best friend, the person you spend the most time with, the person you imagined a future with. But I hope sooner than later you will become your own best friend, invest more time in YOU, and build a future for your own good. I don’t know you, but you seem like a humble and caring woman, surround yourself with as many positive things but hurt as much as you need. Cry as much as you need. It’ll pass. For now, just embrace all the pain and hurt, and you’ll gain wisdom from this soon. Xoxo
